Homepage: https://github.com/Aiven-Open/rohmu

Package: rohmu
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${python3:Depends},
 python3-cryptography (>= 0.8), python3-dateutil, python3-pydantic,
 python3-requests, python3-snappy
Description: Rohmu is a Python library for building backup
 tools for databases providing functionality for compression,
 encryption and transferring data between the database
 and an object storage. Rohmu supports main public clouds
 such as GCP, AWS and Azure for backup storage. Rohmu is
 used in various backup tools such as PGHoard for PostgreSQL,
 MyHoard for MySQL and Astacus for M3 and ClickHouse and
 other databases.
